105
00:07:22,580 --> 00:07:23,280
Wait, Lota.

106
00:07:23,280 --> 00:07:24,520
Nina, hold on a second.

107
00:07:26,300 --> 00:07:29,220
How about the two of us hang out together tonight, you know?

108
00:07:29,480 --> 00:07:30,260
Who, me?

109
00:07:31,300 --> 00:07:32,480
He's made a mistake.

110
00:07:32,880 --> 00:07:34,420
No, be happy about it.

111
00:07:34,700 --> 00:07:36,100
Well, I'd better be going now.

112
00:07:37,260 --> 00:07:38,080
Nina, wait!

113
00:07:38,700 --> 00:07:41,860
Hey, he's really not my type. I mean, not even a little bit.

114
00:07:42,520 --> 00:07:44,440
Stay with me, Nina, please.

115
00:07:46,340 --> 00:07:46,920
Dang it!

116
00:07:51,880 --> 00:07:54,800
It's kind of depressing. I don't think we're fitting in.

117
00:07:55,260 --> 00:07:55,520
Really?

118
00:07:56,040 --> 00:07:57,180
Oh yeah, really.

119
00:07:57,800 --> 00:08:01,380
All those guys were talking to you, but one by one you pushed them away.

120
00:08:01,760 --> 00:08:03,620
Come on, you're way too picky, Nina.

121
00:08:03,940 --> 00:08:06,160
I wasn't consciously trying to be rude.

122
00:08:07,240 --> 00:08:10,600
I guess it's just that... I'm out of practice.

123
00:08:11,240 --> 00:08:11,580
Huh?

124
00:08:11,900 --> 00:08:13,700
These guys all hang out together.

125
00:08:13,700 --> 00:08:19,320
They're used to joking around and having fun, but for me, it's been a long time.

126
00:08:19,740 --> 00:08:21,700
Nina, it sounds like...

127
00:08:28,820 --> 00:08:31,380
You're pretty old-fashioned, despite the way you look.

128
00:08:32,980 --> 00:08:36,500
Despite the way I look? And what exactly is that supposed to mean, Lota?

129
00:08:41,080 --> 00:08:45,860
Hey, guess who's back? Wanna dance with me?

130
00:08:46,200 --> 00:08:47,960
