132
00:08:51,320 --> 00:08:54,540
C'mon, don't be like that. Just one little dance.

133
00:08:55,140 --> 00:08:57,300
Don't come any closer! You're drunk!

134
00:08:57,880 --> 00:09:00,240
Hey, stop it! Let me go!

135
00:09:01,120 --> 00:09:02,500
C'mon, cut it out!

136
00:09:03,360 --> 00:09:07,820
Hey! You know, it's not like I'm asking because I dig you or anything.

137
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:11,080
You're a fine one to talk, buddy. You're just plain rude!

138
00:09:11,340 --> 00:09:14,640
Come on, one stupid little dance. Let's get it over with.

139
00:09:14,780 --> 00:09:16,560
Stop it! Come on, let me go!

140
00:09:16,720 --> 00:09:18,860
If you don't dance with me, then I won't get paid.

141
00:09:19,480 --> 00:09:21,340
Paid? To dance with me?

142
00:09:21,480 --> 00:09:25,740
Yeah, but I'm not supposed to say anything. It's just between Carl and me.

143
00:09:26,120 --> 00:09:29,980
You must have thought you wouldn't be able to find anyone who'd want to dance with you.

144
00:09:30,680 --> 00:09:31,720
Carl did this?

145
00:09:32,500 --> 00:09:33,760
Whatever. I'll dance with you.

146
00:09:33,880 --> 00:09:35,860
So what do you say? Let's hit the dance floor.

147
00:09:36,080 --> 00:09:37,920
I promise not to step on your toes.

148
00:09:38,140 --> 00:09:38,800
Let me go.

149
00:09:39,080 --> 00:09:41,520
Come on, sweetie. I know you don't mean that.

150
00:09:41,540 --> 00:09:42,480
Please, stop it!

151
00:09:42,540 --> 00:09:44,820
Give me one little song and I'm on my way.

152
00:09:49,080 --> 00:09:54,700
Don't! I'm real sorry!

153
00:09:55,940 --> 00:09:57,760
I won't ask anymore, I promise!

154
00:09:58,480 --> 00:10:00,540
Let me go! Come on, please!

155
00:10:02,740 --> 00:10:03,800
We're done.

156
00:10:22,080 --> 00:10:24,220
I must be crazy.

157
00:10:25,500 --> 00:10:27,240
I really liked Carl.

158
00:10:28,080 --> 00:10:30,620
I even helped him get reunited with his father.

159
00:10:32,500 --> 00:10:39,900
so much and I thought he liked me but ever since Mr. Schuwald acknowledged him as his true son he

160
00:10:41,160 --> 00:10:48,560
he has no time for me he's busy with his father it's always his father

161
00:10:53,060 --> 00:11:02,380
I feel so lost it hurts so much I never thought that getting rejected would ever feel like this

162
00:11:03,520 --> 00:11:07,420
It's painful. Right now the world is full of pain.

163
00:11:17,080 --> 00:11:21,000
But everything will be alright. I know it.

164
00:11:21,500 --> 00:11:24,080
The bad things can't keep happening forever.

165
00:11:24,920 --> 00:11:28,500
We have to do our part to stop them. Right?

