211
00:16:48,560 --> 00:16:50,300
to receive your dream prize.

212
00:16:51,260 --> 00:16:52,900
Ready for your first question.

213
00:17:03,460 --> 00:17:06,700
Are you planning to sit here and stare at your food again?

214
00:17:07,280 --> 00:17:09,480
You came in and did that about a week ago.

215
00:17:10,300 --> 00:17:12,720
I make it my business to remember my customers.

216
00:17:13,380 --> 00:17:14,720
If you don't have any appetite,

217
00:17:14,920 --> 00:17:16,740
at least try some soup before you leave.

218
00:17:17,080 --> 00:17:17,940
It's on the house.

219
00:17:19,020 --> 00:17:20,640
Come on, you'd better eat.

220
00:17:21,320 --> 00:17:22,800
Thank you for your concern.

221
00:17:53,260 --> 00:17:54,800
I'll have a clear shot here.

222
00:17:55,780 --> 00:17:57,660
I've got to take him out in this forest.

223
00:18:31,860 --> 00:18:32,340
(gagging)

224
00:18:48,760 --> 00:19:00,040
- Ah, thank goodness.

225
00:19:02,280 --> 00:19:06,100
I know every inch of this forest. I've walked here for so many years.

226
00:19:06,660 --> 00:19:08,140
Well, I must be getting old.

227
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:12,580
You may not have an actual fracture. I've wrapped it up as a precaution.

228
00:19:13,040 --> 00:19:15,080
But you should get an x-ray at the hospital, too.

229
00:19:15,520 --> 00:19:17,420
I didn't peg you as a doctor.

230
00:19:20,560 --> 00:19:24,680
When I first saw you, I thought you were a birdwatcher or maybe a hunter,

231
00:19:24,880 --> 00:19:26,560
but that doesn't seem to be the case.

232
00:19:32,900 --> 00:19:37,320
What are you talking about?

233
00:19:37,880 --> 00:19:38,660
All the birds.

234
00:19:38,980 --> 00:19:39,300
Huh?

235
00:19:39,700 --> 00:19:41,520
They're gathering together overhead.

236
00:19:43,260 --> 00:19:44,620
A long time ago,

237
00:19:44,920 --> 00:19:47,340
all the wild birds would flock together

238
00:19:47,340 --> 00:19:48,780
when a young boy appeared.

239
00:19:49,220 --> 00:19:51,440
He would extend his arm like this

240
00:19:51,440 --> 00:19:53,920
and the birds would come to him.

241
00:19:54,900 --> 00:19:56,540
As a young boy growing up,

242
00:19:56,560 --> 00:19:59,980
he'd spend his free time in the forest with the birds.

243
00:20:01,700 --> 00:20:05,440
But then things changed, and Hitler's era came along.

244
00:20:05,740 --> 00:20:08,740
The boy was now a young man and joined the police force.

245
00:20:09,520 --> 00:20:13,200
He was convinced that the National Socialist German Workers' Party

246
00:20:13,200 --> 00:20:16,540
would turn his bankrupt country into an ideal place.

247
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:20,620
Then out of the blue, this young man was given an order.

248
00:20:21,080 --> 00:20:24,440
A vicious criminal had escaped into this very same forest.

249
00:20:24,440 --> 00:20:29,620
And because he knew these woods so well, he was commanded to go out and find him.

250
00:20:33,120 --> 00:20:35,920
"Shoot the violent criminal on sight," they told him.

251
00:20:36,440 --> 00:20:40,940
The young policeman chased the criminal through the forest that he knew like the back of his hand.

252
00:20:41,200 --> 00:20:44,640
He kept on and on until finally, there he was.

253
00:20:45,200 --> 00:20:47,160
He had him cornered with his hands up.

254
00:20:47,320 --> 00:20:51,740
Then he realized that the vicious criminal was actually just an ordinary man.

255
00:20:52,260 --> 00:20:52,980
A foreigner.

256
00:20:54,600 --> 00:20:59,220
The young man felt he had no choice but to obey without question.

257
00:21:00,220 --> 00:21:02,320
So he carried out his order.

258
00:21:19,320 --> 00:21:23,300
Since that day, the birds never came to rest on his arm again.

259
00:21:24,440 --> 00:21:29,120
For sixty long years now, this man of the forest has been trying to make amends.

260
00:21:29,980 --> 00:21:34,240
I'm sorry. I'm so sorry.

261
00:21:36,040 --> 00:21:40,360
Apologize though he may, the birds refuse to ever come near him.

262
00:21:55,120 --> 00:21:56,500
That's amazing.

263
00:22:01,240 --> 00:22:06,020
It'll be okay now, little bird. It's your home. We respect it.

264
00:22:06,900 --> 00:22:09,640
Never again will blood be shed in this forest.

265
00:22:11,480 --> 00:22:12,900
Isn't that right?

